param

Class CachedFunctionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • param.FunctionFactory
      • param.CachedFunctionFactory

  • final class CachedFunctionFactory
extends FunctionFactory
    Function factory implementing a cache for functions from other factories. This way, each function is only stored in memory once, so as to reduce memory usage and improve speed. This function factory can also use a cache for operations on functions, so that if an operation on the same two functions has already been performed before, the result will be looked up instead of being performed again.
    Author:
    Ernst Moritz Hahn (University of Oxford)
    See Also:
    FunctionFactory, CachedFunction
